  <listingDescription><![CDATA[<p>The skiing here has varied long runs as well as a great selection of tree-lined off-piste. At the top of the slope, you can see the Northern Japan Alps and on a good day you can see the sea. The resort itself is delightful- it started as a hot spring village for resting travellers in the 16th century. Today, the Onsens (bath houses) are still managed by local people and you can trust us when we say that they're the perfect remedy after a day on the slopes. For accommodation, it's up to you how much you want to get into the Japanese culture- you've got both Western and Japanese options.</p>]]></listingDescription>
